      • getPeriod

        public static Period getPeriod(java.lang.String dayBegin,
                               java.lang.String dayEnd,
                               boolean leftClosed,
                               boolean rightClosed)
        Create a period object with given dayBegin and dayEnd as lower and upper bound of the period. Given days will be parsed as a date from 01.01.2018 until 31.01.2018 with time 00:00 in local system time zone

        dayBegin should be lower than dayEnd, valid values: "01"-"31"

        Parameters:
        dayBegin - - day on which the period begins
        dayEnd - - day on which the period ends
        leftClosed - - dayBegin belongs to period if true
        rightClosed - - dayEnd belongs to period if true
        Returns:
        a Period object

      • getMovableFace

        public static MovableFaceIF getMovableFace(double offsetX,
                                           double offsetY)
        Create a 'MovableFace' object without holes.
        The basic 'MovableFace', which would be returned by passing zeros, is a square at the beginning and transforms to a triangle at the end.
        Use the offset parameter to create 'MovableFace' objects with different positions.

        vertices of square: (0,0), (0, 10), (10, 10), (10, 0)
        vertices of triangle: (0,0), (10, 10), (10, 0)
        Parameters:
        offsetX - - move entire MovableFace on the x-axis
        offsetY - - move entire MovableFace on the y-axis
        Returns:
        a 'MovableFace' object without holes

      • getMovableFaceWithHoles

        public static MovableFaceIF getMovableFaceWithHoles(double offsetX,
                                                    double offsetY)
        Create a 'MovableFace' object with two holes.
        The basic 'MovableFace', which would be returned by passing zeros, is a square at the beginning and transforms to a triangle at the end.
        One hole is a constant triangle, the other hole is a square at the beginning and degenerate into one point at the end.
        Use the offset parameter to create 'MovableFace' objects with different positions.

        vertices of square: (0, 0), (0, 10), (10, 10), (10, 0)
        vertices of triangle: (0, 0), (10, 10), (10, 0)
        vertices of hole triangle: (2, 1), (4, 4), (4, 1)
        vertices of hole square: (6, 4), (6, 6), (8, 6), (8, 4) --> (7, 5)
        Parameters:
        offsetX - - move entire MovableFace on the x-axis
        offsetY - - move entire MovableFace on the y-axis
        Returns:
        a 'MovableFace' object without holes

      • getMovableFaceDegenerate

        public static MovableFaceIF getMovableFaceDegenerate(double offsetX,
                                                     double offsetY,
                                                     boolean degeneratesAtEnd)
        Create a 'MovableFace' object without holes which degenerates at the beginning or at the end.
        The basic 'MovableFace', which would be returned by passing zeros, is a square and degenerates at the beginning or at the end into one poit.
        Use the offset parameter to create 'MovableFace' objects with different positions.

        vertices of square: (0,0), (0, 10), (10, 10), (10, 0)
        Parameters:
        offsetX - - move entire MovableFace on the x-axis
        offsetY - - move entire MovableFace on the y-axis
        degeneratesAtEnd - - true - degenerates at the end, false - degenerates at the beginning
        Returns:
        a 'MovableFace' object without holes
